  "issue_title": "Duplicate Issue struct SCALE decoding between contract_client.py and CLI helpers",
  "issue_body": "The Issue struct binary decoding is copy-pasted between `contract_client.py` (`read_issue_from_child_storage`, lines 234-257) and `cli/issue_commands/helpers.py` (`_read_issues_from_child_storage`, lines 807-831). a diff of the two blocks shows a single added comment as the only difference. same for `compute_ink5_lazy_key` \u2014 `contract_client.py:160-165` vs `helpers.py:718-722`, body is identical.\n\nIf the contract struct layout changes, both copies need updating in lockstep. missing one means silent data corruption \u2014 bytes misalign and fields decode to wrong values without any error.\n\nSuggested fix: extract `decode_issue_bytes(data) -> dict` and `compute_ink5_lazy_key(root_key_hex, encoded_key) -> str` into a shared codec module (e.g. `issue_competitions/codec.py`). both callers import from there \u2014 `contract_client.py` wraps the dict into `ContractIssue`, `helpers.py` maps `status_byte` to a name string. zero behavior change.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-15T16:55:04.000Z",
